-- Copper in London Climbs for Second Day to $6,550/Ton, Erases Early Losses
-- Glenys Sim
-- 2010-07-20T01:13:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/copper-in-london-climbs-for-second-day-to-6-550-ton-erases-early-losses.html

          
          
             Copper in London gained for a second
day, by as much as 0.6 percent, to $6,550 a metric ton. The
contract for delivery in three months on the London Metal
Exchange earlier fell as much as 0.2 percent, before trading at
$6,546 a ton by 9:13 a.m. in Singapore.  
          
          


  


        